    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Description\n\noxlint's cmd function\n```lua\n  cmd = function(dispatchers, config)\n    local cmd = 'oxlint'\n    if (config or {}).root_dir then\n      local local_cmd = vim.fs.joinpath(config.root_dir, 'node_modules/.bin', cmd)\n      if vim.fn.executable(local_cmd) == 1 then\n        cmd = local_cmd\n      end\n    end\n    return vim.lsp.rpc.start({ cmd, '--lsp' }, dispatchers)\n  end,\n```\ndoes not check for if nvim is running under win32, and tries to spawn using the bash version instead.\nHere's the error code:\n```\n...s64/ucrt64/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/_transport.lua:68: Spawning language server with cmd: `{ \"C:/path/to/some/projects/node_modules/.bin/oxlint\", \"--lsp\" }` failed. The language server is either not installed, missing from PATH, or not executable.\n```\nI'm using the default configurations from nvim-lspconfig, only capabilities and on_init functions have been modified.\n\nThis fix has worked for me so far\n```lua\n  cmd = function(dispatchers, config)\n    local cmd = 'oxlint'\n    if (config or {}).root_dir then\n      local ext = (vim.fn.has('win32') == 1) and '.cmd' or ''\n      local local_cmd = vim.fs.joinpath(config.root_dir, 'node_modules/.bin', cmd .. ext)\n      if vim.fn.executable(local_cmd) == 1 then\n        cmd = local_cmd\n      end\n    end\n    return vim.lsp.rpc.start({ cmd, '--lsp' }, dispatchers)\n  end,\n```\n\nnvim version\nNVIM v0.12.2\nBuild type: Release\nLuaJIT 2.1.1774896198\nRun \"nvim -V1 -v\" for more info\n\nWindows build:\n10.0.19045 Build 19045\n\nI'm using MSYS2 in UCRT64 runtime. I installed neovim from the command `pacman -S mingw-w64-ucrt-x86_64-neovim`\nI don't know the amount of support neovim has for msys2...\nbash `uname`: `MINGW64_NT-10.0-19045`\n\n`set shell?` = \"C:/msys64/usr/bin/bash.exe\"\n\nMinimal project configuration to repro:\n```bash\nmkdir issue-39298\ncd issue-39298\npnpm init\npnpm add -D oxlint typescript\ncat <<EOF > oxlint.config.ts\nimport { defineConfig } from \"oxlint\";\n\nexport default defineConfig({\n\n})\nEOF\nmkdir src\ncd src\ncat <<EOF > index.ts\nfunction main() {\n    console.log(\"Hello, World!\");\n}\nEOF\nnvim index.ts\n```\n\nRunning \n```lua\n:lua vim.lsp.rpc.start({ \"C:/msys64/home/User/issue-39298/node_modules/.bin/oxlint\", \"--lsp\" })\n```\n\n```\nE5108: Lua: ...s64/ucrt64/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/_transport.lua:68: Spawning language server with cmd: `{ \"C:/msys64/home/User/issue-39298/node_modules/.bin/oxlint\", \"--lsp\" }` failed.\n The language server is either not installed, missing from PATH, or not executable.\nstack traceback:\n        [C]: in function 'error'\n        ...s64/ucrt64/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/_transport.lua:68: in function 'run'\n        C:/msys64/ucrt64/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/rpc.lua:668: in function 'start'\n        [string \":lua\"]:1: in main chunk\n```\n\n",
