            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "I have edited the issue,\n\n```\nRunning MSYS2 bash before opening neovim:\n    Manually:\n      - vim.o.shell = \"C:\\\\msys64\\\\usr\\\\bin\\\\bash.exe\" -- Default\n        vim.o.shellcmdflag = \"-c\"\n        vim.o.shellxquote = \"\"\n\n        :lua vim.lsp.rpc.start({ \"C:/msys64/home/User/issue-39298/node_modules/.bin/oxlint\", \"--lsp\" }) -> ❌ Error\n        :lua vim.lsp.rpc.start({ \"C:/msys64/home/User/issue-39298/node_modules/.bin/oxlint.CMD\", \"--lsp\" }) -> ✅ No error\n\n      - vim.o.shell = \"cmd.exe\"\n        vim.o.shellcmdflag = \"/s /c\"\n        vim.o.shellxquote = \"\\\"\"\n\n        :lua vim.lsp.rpc.start({ \"C:/msys64/home/User/issue-39298/node_modules/.bin/oxlint\", \"--lsp\" }) -> ✅ No error\n        :lua vim.lsp.rpc.start({ \"C:/msys64/home/User/issue-39298/node_modules/.bin/oxlint.CMD\", \"--lsp\" }) -> ✅ No error\n\n    Automatically (opening a .ts file):\n      - vim.o.shell = \"C:\\\\msys64\\\\usr\\\\bin\\\\bash.exe\" -- Default\n        vim.o.shellcmdflag = \"-c\"\n        vim.o.shellxquote = \"\"\n\n        cmd: C:/msys64/home/User/issue-39298/node_modules/.bin/oxlint\n        result: ❌ ...s64/ucrt64/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/_transport.lua:68: Spawning language server with cmd: `{ \"C:/msys64/home/User/issue-39298/node_modules/.bin/oxlint\", \"--lsp\" }` failed. The language server is either not installed, missing from PATH, or not executable.\n\n      - vim.o.shell = \"cmd.exe\"\n        vim.o.shellcmdflag = \"/s /c\"\n        vim.o.shellxquote = \"\\\"\"\n\n        cmd: C:/msys64/home/User/issue-39298/node_modules/.bin/oxlint\n        result: ✅ No error\n\nRunning Powershell before opening neovim:\n    Manually:\n      - vim.o.shell = \"cmd.exe\" -- Default\n        vim.o.shellcmdflag = \"/s /c\" -- Default\n        vim.o.shellxquote = \"\\\"\" -- Default\n\n        :lua vim.lsp.rpc.start({ \"C:/msys64/home/User/issue-39298/node_modules/.bin/oxlint\", \"--lsp\" }) -> ✅ No error\n        :lua vim.lsp.rpc.start({ \"C:/msys64/home/User/issue-39298/node_modules/.bin/oxlint.CMD\", \"--lsp\" }) -> ✅ No error\n\n      - vim.o.shell = \"C:\\\\msys64\\\\usr\\\\bin\\\\bash.exe\"\n        vim.o.shellcmdflag = \"-c\"\n        vim.o.shellxquote = \"\"\n\n        :lua vim.lsp.rpc.start({ \"C:/msys64/home/User/issue-39298/node_modules/.bin/oxlint\", \"--lsp\" }) -> ❌ Error\n        :lua vim.lsp.rpc.start({ \"C:/msys64/home/User/issue-39298/node_modules/.bin/oxlint.CMD\", \"--lsp\" }) -> ✅ No error\n\n     Automatically (opening a .ts file):\n      - vim.o.shell = \"cmd.exe\" -- Default\n        vim.o.shellcmdflag = \"/s /c\" -- Default\n        vim.o.shellxquote = \"\\\"\" -- Default\n\n        cmd: C:/msys64/home/User/issue-39298/node_modules/.bin/oxlint\n        result: ✅ No error\n\n      - vim.o.shell = \"C:\\\\msys64\\\\usr\\\\bin\\\\bash.exe\"\n        vim.o.shellcmdflag = \"-c\"\n        vim.o.shellxquote = \"\"\n\n        cmd: C:/msys64/home/User/issue-39298/node_modules/.bin/oxlint\n        result: ❌ ...s64/ucrt64/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/_transport.lua:68: Spawning language server with cmd: `{ \"C:/msys64/home/User/issue-39298/node_modules/.bin/oxlint\", \"--lsp\" }` failed. The language server is either not installed, missing from PATH, or not executable.\n\n```\n\nSomething is wrong with msys's bash with vim.lsp.rpc...\n\n```\nIn `node_modules/.bin/` directory:\n\nwith files: [\"oxlint\", \"oxlint.CMD\"]\ncmd.exe:\n    >>> .\\oxlint\n    ✅ No error\n    >>> .\\oxlint.CMD\n    ✅ No error\nbash.exe:\n    >>> ./oxlint\n    ✅ No error\n    >>> ./oxlint.CMD\n    ✅ No error\n\nwith files: [\"oxlint\"]\ncmd.exe:\n    >>> .\\oxlint\n    '.\\oxlint' is not recognized as an internal or external command,\n    operable program or batch file.\n    >>> .\\oxlint.CMD\n    '.\\oxlint.CMD' is not recognized as an internal or external command,\n    operable program or batch file.\nbash.exe:\n    >>> ./oxlint\n    ✅ No error\n    >>> ./oxlint.CMD\n    bash: ./oxlint.CMD: No such file or directory\n\nwith files: [\"oxlint.CMD\"]\ncmd.exe:\n    >>> .\\oxlint\n    ✅ No error\n    >>> .\\oxlint.CMD\n    ✅ No error\nbash.exe:\n    >>> ./oxlint\n    bash: ./oxlint: No such file or directory\n    >>> ./oxlint.CMD\n    ✅ No error\n```\n\nSeems like cmd.exe appends .CMD whenever possible.",
