        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> we treat `bash.exe` as a Unix shell, so `exepath` returns a path without the file extension, which causes `spawn` to fail\n\nwhy does it fail without the path extension? shouldn't that work if the shell is bash?",
            "created_at": "2026-05-07T10:47:05Z",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/39298#issuecomment-4396427822",
            "id": 4396427822,
