        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "This path doesn't get processed by `bash.exe`, it's passed directly to `uv.spawn`(`CreateProcess`), and this api requires the filename to have an extension. Or in other words, this path is never invoked through that shell(e.g., `bash.exe -c \"oxlint --lsp\"`; instead, it is passed directly to `uv.spawn` as the executable.\n\nBTW, even though `libuv` has a `UV_PROCESS_WINDOWS_FILE_PATH_EXACT_NAME` flag, it doesn't apply to this issue (ref https://gitlab.kitware.com/cmake/cmake/-/work_items/25450#note_1451473).\n\n<img width=\"3354\" height=\"398\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/60bccbc8-5664-4e4a-92ed-c90014137512\" />\n\n[windows doc:](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/win32/api/processthreadsapi/nf-processthreadsapi-createprocessa#parameters)\n> This parameter must include the file name extension; no default extension is assumed.",
            "created_at": "2026-05-07T11:06:21Z",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/39298#issuecomment-4396550942",
